What is Ingress?
Ingress is a Kubernetes resource that defines rules for routing external HTTP/HTTPS traffic to services inside the cluster.

What is Ingress Controller?
It is the component that implements Ingress rules and handles the actual traffic routing.

Why do we need Ingress?
To provide a single entry point, reduce cost, and enable advanced routing and TLS termination.

Service → gives access  
Ingress → controls how traffic flows  
Ingress Controller → executes routing  

>> TLS Termination is the process where encrypted HTTPS traffic is decrypted at a specific point (like an Ingress Controller or Load Balancer) before being forwarded to backend services.

User (HTTPS request 🔒)
        ↓
Ingress Controller (decrypts TLS 🔓)
        ↓
Service (HTTP)
        ↓
Pod

User sends HTTPS request
Ingress receives encrypted traffic
Ingress uses SSL certificate to decrypt
Forwards plain HTTP to backend